msgid "Glossary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:8
msgid "OpenNebula Components"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:10
msgid "**Front-end**: Machine running the OpenNebula services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:11
msgid ""
"**Host**: Physical machine running a supported hypervisor. See the "
":ref:`Host subsystem <hostsubsystem>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:12
msgid ""
"**Cluster**: Pool of hosts that share datastores and virtual networks. "
"Clusters are used for load balancing, high availability, and high "
"performance computing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:13
msgid ""
"**Image Repository**: Storage for registered Images. Learn more about the "
":ref:`Storage subsystem <sm>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:14
msgid ""
"**Sunstone**: OpenNebula web interface. Learn more about :ref:`Sunstone "
"<sunstone>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:15
msgid ""
"**OCCI Service**: Server that enables the management of OpenNebula with OCCI"
" interface. Learn more about :ref:`OCCI Service <occicg>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:16
msgid ""
"**Self-Service** OpenNebula web interfaced towards the end user. It is "
"implemented by configuring a user view of the Sunstone Portal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:17
msgid ""
"**EC2 Service**: Server that enables the management of OpenNebula with EC2 "
"interface. Learn more about :ref:`EC2 Service <ec2qcg>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:18
msgid ""
"**OCA**: OpenNebula Cloud API. It is a set of libraries that ease the "
"communication with the XML-RPC management interface. Learn more about "
":ref:`ruby <ruby>` and :ref:`java <java>` APIs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:21
msgid "OpenNebula Resources"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:23
msgid ""
"**Template**: Virtual Machine definition. These definitions are managed with"
" the :ref:`onetemplate command <vm_guide>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:24
msgid ""
"**Image**: Virtual Machine disk image, created and managed with the "
":ref:`oneimage command <img_guide>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:25
msgid ""
"**Virtual Machine**: Instantiated Template. A Virtual Machine represents one"
" life-cycle, and several Virtual Machines can be created from a single "
"Template. Check out the :ref:`VM management guide <vm_guide_2>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:26
msgid ""
"**Virtual Network**: A group of IP leases that VMs can use to automatically "
"obtain IP addresses. See the :ref:`Networking subsystem <nm>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:27
msgid ""
"**VDC**: Virtual Data Center, fully-isolated virtual infrastructure "
"environments where a group of users, under the control of the VDC "
"administrator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:28
msgid ""
"**Zone**: A group of interconnected physical hosts with hypervisors "
"controlled by OpenNebula."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:31
msgid "OpenNebula Management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:33
msgid ""
"**ACL**: Access Control List. Check :ref:`the managing ACL rules guide "
"<manage_acl>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:34
msgid ""
"**oneadmin**: Special administrative account. See the :ref:`Users and Groups"
" guide <manage_users>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design_and_installation/building_your_cloud/glossary.rst:35
msgid ""
"**Federation**: Several OpenNebula instances can be :ref:`configured as "
"zones <introf>`."
msgstr ""
